Class BezierEdgePlacer

java.lang.Object
  presentation.fsa.BezierEdgePlacer

public class BezierEdgePlacer
extends java.lang.Object

Algorithms for laying out a Bezier edge among a set of existing edges connecting the same pair of nodes. FIXME In some cases, the placed edge increases its arc one more time than required.

Author:
Helen Bretzke for DES Lab, Dept of ECE, Queen's University, Kingston 13 August 2006

insertEdgeAmong

public static void insertEdgeAmong(BezierEdge edge,
                                   java.util.Set<Edge> otherEdges)
Inserts edge among the given set of other edges, where all edges connect the same pair of nodes. Computes the layouts for each edge such that they are distributed comfortably along the circumferences of each end node. TODO change this algorithm so that it accommodates reflexive edges and initial arrows (adjacent on only one of edge's end nodes).

Parameters:
edge - the edge to be inserted
otherEdges - set of all other edges connecting the same pair of nodes

setToOutermostFreeLayout

private static BezierLayout setToOutermostFreeLayout(Edge edge,
                                                     java.util.Set<Edge> otherEdges)
Returns the layout for, and sets edge's layout to, the outermost free position such that the arcs of all edges in otherEdges are flatter. NOTE Outermost is defined as having the greatest arc in the curve.

Parameters:
edge - the edge to be laid out
otherEdges - set of all other edges connecting the same pair of nodes
Returns:
the layout for the first free outermost position
See Also:
??? Precondition: there is already a straight edge in edges. else why wouldn't we just make a straight edge...

findOutermostTakenPosition

private static BezierLayout findOutermostTakenPosition(java.util.Set<Edge> edges)
Returns the layout for the outermost non-flat, occupied edge layout among edges if all edges are flat, returns a flat layout. NOTE Outermost is defined as having the greatest arc in the curve.

Parameters:
edges - the set of edges
Returns:
the layout for the outermost non-flat, occupied edge layout among edges. If all edges are flat, returns a flat layout.
See Also:
Precondition: edges is not empty
